Bug ID: #01 - Click VS Drag Conflict
Status: Resolved
Reporter: Kyaw Sis Thway
Debugger: Luaegyigyi
Description: The logic currently used for mouse operation has a major problem. 
                It cannot distinguish between drag and click. After the introduction of isClicker type entity,
                their dual functions are in conflict according to current logic. BreadPlate can be clicked three times and the outline
                color will change according to how many times it has been clicked. But now, it can only be clicked once and the later
                result all become drag mechanic.
Steps to Reproduce:
    Start the game.
    Drag LoafOfBread from BreadBasket to BreadPlate.
    Click BreadPlate once.
    Click again.
Expected Result: The color of the outline doesn't change from yellow to orange, which is the second stage representing two slices.
Actual Result:  The color remains yellow. Drag SliceOfBread to SandwichPlate. The yellow outline becomes transparent proving
                that its count is now 0.

Bug ID: #02 - Order Logic Validation
Status: Resolved
Reporter: Ko Kyaw Sis Thway
Debugger: Luaegyigyi
Description: The game logic failed to verify if the item delivered by the player matched the
             customer's specific request. Customers would accept and pay for any item (e.g., giving Bread
             when they asked for Coffee).
Steps to Reproduce:
     Start the game and wait for a customer to request COFFEE.
     Pick up a SLICE OF BREAD or SANDWICH.
     Interact with the customer.
     Observe that the item is accepted and payment is received regardless of the request.
Expected Result:The customer should only accept the item if the Player Item ID matches the Customer Request ID.
                If the items do not match, the customer should reject the item and no payment should be processed. 
Actual Result:  The customer accepted all items as "Correct," leading to a logic error where any product could be sold to satisfy any order.     

Bug ID: #03 - Ordering Process Logic Errors
Status: Resolved
Reporter: Kyaw Sis Thway
Debugger: Luaegyigyi
Description: The ordering system is failing in two ways: 
                 customers are requesting items that aren't unlocked yet for the current day, and 
                 they are immediately leaving the shop if handed the wrong item instead of waiting for a correction.
Steps to Reproduce:
    Start the game.
    Observe if a customer requests an item not yet unlocked
    If they request a valid item, intentionally give them the wrong order type.
Expected Result: Customers only request unlocked items and remain at the counter until their patience runs out or the correct order is served and patience is decrease.
Actual Result:  Customers request "future" items and despawn immediately upon receiving an incorrect order.

Bug ID: #04 - Plate State Conflict (Loaf vs. Slice)
Status: Resolved 
Reporter: Luaegyigyi
Debugger: Luaegyigyi
Description: The player is unable to place or drag a full "Loaf" onto a plate if that plate already contains a "Slice." 
                 This prevents fulfilling orders for customers wanting a full Loaf if a slice was previously prepared or left over.
Steps to Reproduce:
    Start the game.
    Place a "Slice" of bread onto an empty plate.
    Attempt to drag a "Loaf" from the source/inventory onto that same plate.
Expected Result: The player should be able to place a Loaf even if a slice is present. 
Actual Result:  The Loaf cannot be dragged/placed, effectively "locking" the plate or preventing the Loaf order from being completed.
Actual Result:  The customer accepted all items as "Correct," leading to a logic error where any product could be sold to satisfy any order.            

Bug ID: #05 - Developer Command
Status: Resolved
Reporter: Kyaw Sis Thway
Debugger: Luaegyigyi
Description: Although the PopupWindow is added, the developer function is so buggy it isn't recommended for use yet.
Steps to Reproduce:
     Start the game and press k at any game state.
     Enter \dev skip (number) or \dev money (number).
Expected Result: The result should directly interact with the game and influence it so that developer has easier time 
                navigating the game.
Actual Result:  Random things keep on popping while using developer mode. Determined that it is of low priority and
                leave the bug.

Bug ID: #06 - Machine Unlock
Status: Resolved
Reporter: Kyaw Sis Thway
Debugger:Luaegyigyi
Description: It seems that after quiting at DayEndState, the next saved play will 
            have difficulty in accessing what is available and not.
Steps to Reproduce:
     Start the game.
     Start a new game.
     Quit at DayEndState.
     Restart the game and press play.
Expected Result: Day 2. So, loaf should be unlocked.
Actual Result:  Missing.

